snippet: The redistricting might flip a few House seats in the 2016 election, including one held by Representative Daniel Webster, who is vying to become speaker.
abstract: Florida's Second Circuit Court Judge Terry P Lewis rejects congressional district maps drawn by Republican Legislature and approves those submitted by coalition of voter-rights groups; decision, if approved by State Supreme Court, may flip some seats from Republican to Democrat in 2016 election.
lead_paragraph: The redistricting might flip a few House seats in the 2016 election, including one held by Representative Daniel Webster, who is vying to become speaker.

headline.print_headline: Judge Picks Voting Map in Florida
